# bo-orc-ms — your overrides.
#
# Loaded AFTER bo-orc.defaults.env. LLM_PROVIDER / LLM_MODEL / LLM_API_KEY
# come from quickstart/.env via compose `environment:` — set them there,
# not here.
#
# Examples:
#   LOG_AGENT_PAYLOADS=no                       # quieter agent logs
#   AGENT_HIGH_STAKES_TOOLS=person_invite,...   # extend HITL gating
#   AGENT_CHECKPOINTER=redis  + REDIS_URL=...   # persistent agent state
#
# ─── Local / OpenAI-compatible LLM (Ollama, LM Studio, vLLM, …) ──────────────
# LLM_BASE_URL is the ONE LLM var you set here, not in quickstart/.env: it is
# only valid when LLM_PROVIDER=openai-compatible and is rejected otherwise, so
# it cannot be forwarded with an empty default the way the cloud vars are.
# Uncomment the line below (and in quickstart/.env set LLM_PROVIDER=openai-
# compatible, LLM_MODEL=<tag>, LLM_API_KEY=ollama) to point the agent at a
# local runtime. The URL must include the /v1 path segment.
#
# The runtime runs on the HOST, but bo-orc runs in a container — so use
# host.docker.internal, not localhost. On a Linux host, also add
#   extra_hosts: ["host.docker.internal:host-gateway"]
# to bo-orc-ms (compose overlay) so that name resolves.
#
#   LLM_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434/v1   # Ollama default port
